|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The minister of health reported that the total number of the death is still 5, the same as that on 14 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172?tag_from=wp_cb_mostPopular_list&_ga=2.238927360.105839233.1584339272-1415494084.1580723020|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|last=detikcom|first=tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> while two new deaths were reported in the early morning by Governor of Central Java<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-4942759/1-pasien-positif-corona-meninggal-di-rs-kariadi-semarang-hari-ini|title=1 Pasien Positif Corona Meninggal di RS Kariadi Semarang Hari Ini|last=Purbaya|first=Angling Adhitya|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> and Governor of Banten.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942389/gubernur-banten-1-pasien-positif-corona-di-pondok-aren-meninggal|title=Gubernur Banten: 1 Pasien Positif Corona di Pondok Aren Meninggal|last=Komara|first=Indra|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The total number of deaths should be 7.\n\n====18 March====\n*Indonesia confirmed 55 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total up to 227 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944276/update-terbaru-virus-corona-di-indonesia-total-kasus-positif-jadi-227-orang|title=Update Terbaru Virus Corona di Indonesia: Total Kasus Positif Jadi 227 Orang|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*12 patients died, the number of deaths has now increased to 19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944358/pernyataan-lengkap-pemerintah-soal-227-kasus-positif-corona-dan-19-meninggal|title=Pernyataan Lengkap Pemerintah soal 227 Kasus Positif Corona dan 19 Meninggal|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> The 19 fatalities mean that Indonesia has now recorded the highest death toll among Southeast Asian countries hit by the coronavirus to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/18/covid-19-indonesia-records-highest-death-toll-in-southeast-asia-at-19.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesia records highest death toll in Southeast Asia at 19|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Indonesia's case fatality rate has reached 8.37% which is double the world case fatality rate (4.07%).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944800/tingkat-kematian-pasien-corona-di-ri-837-bagaimana-negara-lain|title=Tingkat Kematian Pasien Corona di RI 8,37%, Bagaimana Negara Lain?|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*7 Indonesians in [[India]] tested positive for COVID-19 were a part of a 10-member team who travelled to [[Karimnagar]] for a religious tour.<ref name=\"TH1\">{{cite news |last1=Geetanath |first1=K. Shiva Shankar & V. |title=Coronavirus {{!}} Telangana reports 8 new COVID-19 cases |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/telangana-reports-8-new-covid-19-cases/article31102733.ece?homepage=true |newspaper=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*After 2 positive cases, Governor of West Kalimantan [[Sutarmidji]] declares an \"extraordinary event\" until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944658/ada-2-kasus-positif-gubernur-tetapkan-kalbar-klb-corona|title=Ada 2 Kasus Positif, Gubernur Tetapkan Kalbar KLB Corona|last=Kholid|first=Idham|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n====19 March====\n* Joko Widodo announces 7 critical points (mass rapid tests, incentive for medical personnel, involve religious people, stop exporting medical equipment, stop ho