ths, an increase of 7 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947188/data-terbaru-369-positif-corona-meningkat-60-kasus|title=Data Terbaru: 369 Positif Corona, Meningkat 60 Kasus|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Indonesia Minister of State-Owned Enterprises [[Erick Thohir]] that Indonesia has enough drugs for 60,000 COVID-19 patients, and by the end of March could supply up to 4.7 million face masks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4947190/erick-thohir-obat-pasien-corona-bisa-untuk-60-ribu-orang|title=Erick Thohir: Obat Pasien Corona Bisa untuk 60 Ribu Orang|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo instructed his officials to shift budgetary priorities. Less prioritized budgets from the state budget (APBN) and regional budget (APBD) are to be reallocated to fund government efforts in combating the coronavirus pandemic, increasing the safety net for Indonesians, and to incentivize small and medium businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibizmedia.com/2020/03/20/hadapi-tantangan-pandemi-covid-19-ini-tiga-prioritas-kerja-pemerintah/|title=Hadapi Tantangan Pandemi Covid-19, Ini Tiga Prioritas Kerja Pemerintah|last=Sinambela|first=Maruli|date=2020-03-20|website=Vibizmedia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> He also promised to begin deploying rapid coronavirus testing, prioritizing South Jakarta as the worst-hit area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947166/pemerintah-mulai-rapid-test-corona-hari-ini-jakarta-jadi-prioritas|title=Pemerintah Mulai Rapid Test Corona Hari Ini, Jakarta Jadi Prioritas|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Anies Baswedan declares a state of emergency in Jakarta for the next 14 days (2 April).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947518/c