mative Years of a King''. Stroud, Gloucestershire: Sutton Publishing. {{ISBN|0-7509-2398-9}}.\n* Claydon, Tony (2008). \"[http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-29450 William III and II]\" ''Oxford Dictionary of National Biography'', online ed. Oxford University Press.\n* [[Tom Devine|Devine, T. M.]] (2006). ''The Scottish Nation 1700\u20132007''. London: Penguin Books. {{ISBN|0-14-102769-X}}.\n* Harris, Tim (2006). ''Revolution: The Great Crisis of the British Monarchy, 1685\u20131720''. Penguin Books. {{ISBN|0-7139-9759-1}}.\n* Hilliam, David (1998). ''Kings, Queens, Bones & Bastards''. Stroud, Gloucestershire: Sutton Publishing. {{ISBN|0-7509-3553-7}}.\n* Jones, J. R. (1988). ''The Revolution of 1688 in England''. Weidenfeld and Nicolson. {{ISBN|0-297-99467-0}}.\n* [[John Phillipps Kenyon|Kenyon, J. P.]] (1986). ''The Stuart Constitution 1603\u20131688, Documents and Commentary'', 2nd ed. Cambridge University Press. {{ISBN|0-521-31327-9}}.\n* {{cite book|last=Louda|first=Ji\u0159\u00ed|authorlink=Ji\u0159\u00ed Louda|last2=Maclagan|first2=Michael|authorlink2=Michael Maclagan|year=1999|origyear=1981|title=Lines of Succession: Heraldry of the Royal Families of Europe|edition=2nd|location=London|publisher=Little, Brown|isbn=978-0-316-84820-6|ref=harv}}\n* MacLeod, John (1999). ''Dynasty, the Stuarts, 1560\u20131807''. London: Hodder and Stoughton. {{ISBN|0-340-70767-4}}.\n* [[Thomas Babington Macaulay, 1st Baron Macaulay|Macaulay, Thomas Babington]] (1889). ''[[The History of England from the Accession of James the Second]]. [https://books.google.com/books?id=1oIYAAAAYAAJ Popular Edition in Two Volumes]''. London: Longmans.\n* Mann, Alastair (2014). ''James VII: Duke and King of Scots, 1633\u20131701''. Edinburgh: John Donald.\n* Miller, John (2000). ''James II'', 3rd ed. {{ISBN|0-300-08728-4}}.\n* McFerran, Noel S. (2003). [http://jacobite.ca/kings/james2.htm \"James II and VII.\"]\n* \u00d3 Buachalla, Breand\u00e